Python Virtual Environments (venv)

An isolated environment per project: own site-packages, avoids version clashes with other projects.

Create (in project folder):
  Windows:  python -m venv myenv
  macOS/Linux: python3 -m venv myenv

Activate:
  Windows CMD:  myenv\Scripts\activate.bat
  Windows PS:   myenv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
  macOS/Linux:  source myenv/bin/activate

Then install with pip (only into this env). Deactivate: deactivate
Remove env: delete the folder (or rmdir /s /q on Windows, rm -rf on Unix).

See also: https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_virtualenv.asp
